As a result of this value (calculation on next page) it can be reduced to units of gram per
centimeter-square root of atoms. One may ask what are grams per centimeter? Grams, or
mass, occupy a volume, such as cubic centimeters. However, as shown in the sketch, we will
consider grams per centimeter to represent the number of atoms on a line, even though mass
is three dimensional and therefore cannot ﬁt on a line which is two dimensional. However, we
can use it as a mathematical convenience. One may ask what are square root atoms. Let us
consider atoms to be the number of atoms in a two dimensional surface, even though, again
they are three dimensional and therefore occupy space. As such, the square root of atoms is
the number of atoms on each side of the square unit making the surface.!
